"title": "6109: alienation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6109: alienation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A state of being separate or apart from something or someone, often accompanied by an awareness of the separation. Human beings are alienated from God on account of sin. Alienation is also encountered in other areas of life, including relations between believers, and between believers and secular society.</p>\n<h2>Alienation from God because of sin</h2>\n<h3>Sin causes separation from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:4\">GAL 5:4</a></strong> <em>Those seeking to justify themselves cut themselves off from Jesus Christ's saving work</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21\">COL 1:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1-Isa59:2\">ISA 59:1–59:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:23-Ezek39:24\">EZK 39:23–39:24</a></p>\n<h3>Seen in discomfort in God's presence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8-Gen3:10\">GEN 3:8–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:8\">LUK 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>Seen in defeat in battle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:42\">DEU 1:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:41-Num14:45\">NUM 14:41–14:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:11-Josh7:12\">JOS 7:11–7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:11-Judg2:15\">JDG 2:11–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Seen in unanswered prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1-Isa59:2\">ISA 59:1–59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:45\">DEU 1:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:18\">PSA 66:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:28-Prov1:30\">PRO 1:28–1:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15\">ISA 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Seen in unaccepted worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11-Isa1:14\">ISA 1:11–1:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:21-Amos5:23\">AMO 5:21–5:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:10\">MAL 1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Seen in lost closeness with God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23-Gen3:24\">GEN 3:23–3:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:3\">EXO 33:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:6\">EZK 8:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:6\">HOS 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:3\">JON 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>A sense of alienation from God</h2>\n<h3>Feelings of alienation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:14\">ISA 49:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:12\">PSA 39:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:3-Ps42:4\">PSA 42:3–42:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:9-Ps42:10\">PSA 42:9–42:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:23-Ps44:24\">PSA 44:23–44:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:27\">ISA 40:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:1\">LAM 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a> <em>Jesus Christ's alienation from God as he bore the consequences of human sin was felt and actual.</em></p>\n<h3>The reassurance of God's concern</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15-Isa49:16\">ISA 49:15–49:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1-Isa43:5\">ISA 43:1–43:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:21\">ISA 44:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:7\">ISA 54:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:20\">JER 31:20</a></p>\n<h2>Alienation from others</h2>\n<h3>Alienation caused by a third party</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:28\">PRO 16:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:9\">PRO 17:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:17\">GAL 4:17</a> <em>False teachers in Galatia tried to drive a wedge between Paul and the church.</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of alienation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:7\">GEN 3:7</a> <em>Man and woman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:3-Gen4:8\">GEN 4:3–4:8</a> <em>Cain and Abel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:41\">GEN 27:41</a> <em>Jacob and Esau</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:8-1Sam18:9\">1SA 18:8–18:9</a> <em>Saul and David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:13-Job19:19\">JOB 19:13–19:19</a> <em>Job and his family and friends</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:8\">PSA 69:8</a> <em>the psalmist and his family</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:6\">JER 12:6</a> <em>Jeremiah and his family</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:39\">ACT 15:39</a> <em>Paul and Barnabas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:12\">EPH 2:12</a> <em>Jew and Gentile</em></p>\n<h2>Overcoming alienation</h2>\n<h3>Being reconciled to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:11\">ROM 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:18–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:25\">1PE 2:25</a></p>\n<h3>Reconciliation with others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:18\">LEV 19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:23-Matt5:24\">MAT 5:23–5:24</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of reconciliation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:4\">GEN 33:4</a> <em>Jacob and Esau</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:19-Gen50:21\">GEN 50:19–50:21</a> <em>Joseph and his brothers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:16\">EPH 2:14–2:16</a> <em>Jew and Gentile</em></p>\n<h2>God's people are aliens in the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:18-John15:19\">JHN 15:18–15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:16\">JHN 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:13-Heb11:16\">HEB 11:13–11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Responsibility to the alien</h2>\n<h3>God's concern for the outsider</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:9\">PSA 146:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:18\">DEU 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:17\">JER 30:17</a></p>\n<h3>The example of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10-Matt9:11\">MAT 9:10–9:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15-Mark2:16\">MRK 2:15–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29-Luke5:30\">LUK 5:29–5:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ welcomed those who had been alienated by the rest of society.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:2-Matt8:3\">MAT 8:2–8:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:42\">MRK 1:40–1:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:13\">LUK 5:12–5:13</a> <em>Jesus Christ touched the “untouchable” man with leprosy</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:19\">MAT 11:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:34\">LUK 7:34</a></p>\n<h3>Equal treatment for the alien</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:34\">LEV 19:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:48-Exod12:49\">EXO 12:48–12:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:22\">LEV 24:22</a></p>\n<h3>Ensuring justice for the alien</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17\">DEU 24:17</a></strong> <em>The weaker members of Israelite society are of special concern.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:3\">JER 22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:9-Zech7:10\">ZEC 7:9–7:10</a></p>\n<h3>Special provision for the alien</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:22\">LEV 23:22</a></strong> <em>God makes special provision for the poor so that they will have a share in the blessings of the land.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:10\">LEV 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:20\">DEU 24:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:28-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:28–14:29</a> <em>The third year's tithe is shared with those without inheritance in the land.</em></p>",
